<br>
Our membership consists of some of the most skilled players in the game. A certain level of maturity and dedication is expected of anyone who wishes to join our ranks. We are a <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>raiding guild</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> and it is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">not</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the guild for a casual player. If you do not have the time to play 4 nights a week out of 7, we are not the guild for you. We seek to kill every mob in the game. We need players that not only enjoy the game, but are also serious about it. <br>
<br>
We accept only level 65 players and only those who consider everquest their primary past time, spending at minimum 30 hours per week playing. We typically run raids from the time period between 6pm - 2am EST daily. On occasion we do have free nights when spawns are not up. <br>
<br>
<br>
To apply, you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>must</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> meet the following qualifications:<br>
<br>
* Level 65<br>
* At least 100 AA's, the more you have, the better.<br>
* Playtime <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>exceeding</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> 30hrs per week<br>
* Online during EST - PST peak times (6pm - 2am EST).<br>
* Usual assortment of resist gear / keys / utility gear, including an eb item<br>
* All expansions up to PoP<br>
* Familiar with /loc and able to get around in every zone in the game<br>
* Innate Run Speed III<br>
* Flagged for PoS/PoV, BoT, HoHa, CoD, PoNb. The more flags to elementals, the better your chances.<br>
* Completed Emperor key, Vex Thal Key - or at least 50% done with each. <br>
<br>
Our needs are : <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;">Bards - High<br>
Beastlords - Closed<br>
Clerics - Low<br>
Druids - Low <br>
Enchanters - Low<br>
Magicians - Closed<br>
Monks - High<br>
Necromancers - Closed<br>
Paladins - Low<br>
Rangers - Low<br>
Rogues - Low<br>
Shadowknight - Closed<br>
Shaman - Closed<br>
Warriors - Closed<br>
Wizards -  High</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Please do NOT post an application unless you meet the above requirements</span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
If you do decide to post, please use this format to be considered: <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:white;">Char. Name: <br>
Class:<br>
Level: <br>
AA's : <br>
Is this your Character that you leveled from level 1, or did you get it by other means. If so, explain.<br>
Completed Keys and Flags: <br>
How well do you know your Class?<br>
What has been your most memorable EQ experience so far?<br>
Experience in hard core raiding: <br>
Anyone you know in NE? <br>
Type of Connection :<br>
Usual Play time and time zone: <br>
Why do you wish to join NE? <br>
Can you handle criticism?<br>
Are you easily offended by off color humor/joking? <br>
Include your Magelo link.<br>
Is there anything you would like to share with us to know you better? </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<br>
If you cannot at least follow this format and be detailed in your answers, your application will <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be considered.<br>
<br>
Once we have gotten in touch with you and if you are tagged as an app, your application will then be moved to App Review for member voting. For a period of about 2 - 4 weeks you will be an applicant and your application will be &quot;closed&quot; in that section. This is your time to do your best to impress the officers and the members with your play time and abilities. After those weeks, the members vote on whether you do become a full member or not. Two or more &quot;no&quot; votes will disqualify you from becoming a full member and you will be notified by an officer and guild removed. If voting is in your favor, then you will become a full member. <br>
<br>
During your time as an app, you do receive dkp points. You will not be able to roll on loot unless no full member wants it, then you may roll and receive loot. <br>
